<td style="width: 24em" id="mwQg">• "[M]editation refers to a family of self-regulation practices that focus on training attention and awareness in order to bring mental processes under greater voluntary control and thereby foster general mental well-being and development and/or specific capacities such as calm, clarity, and concentration"<sup about="#mwt81" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-walsh06_1-1" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{"name":"walsh06"}}'><a href="./Meditation#cite_note-walsh06-1" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 1;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[1]</span></a></sup><sup class="reference" style="white-space:nowrap;" about="#mwt79" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"rp","href":"./Template:Rp"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"228–29"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwQw">:<span>228–29</span></sup></td>
