<tr valign="top" id="mwSg">
<td id="mwSw">• "We define meditation... as a stylized mental technique... repetitively practiced for the purpose of attaining a subjective experience that is frequently described as very restful, silent, and of heightened alertness, often characterized as blissful"<sup about="#mwt91" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-jevning92_3-1" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{"name":"jevning92"}}'><a href="./Meditation#cite_note-jevning92-3" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 3;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[3]</span></a></sup><sup class="reference" style="white-space:nowrap;" about="#mwt89" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"rp","href":"./Template:Rp"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"415"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwTA">:<span>415</span></sup></td>
