id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-16" class="mw-reference-text"> The verb root "dhyai" is listed as referring to "contemplate, meditate on" and "dhyāna" is listed as referring to "meditation; religious contemplation" on page 134 of <cite class="citation book" about="#mwt51" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"A practical Sanskrit dictionary with transliteration, accentuation and etymological analysis throughout"},"last":{"wt":"Macdonell"},"first":{"wt":"Arthur Anthony"},"authorlink":{"wt":"Arthur Anthony Macdonell"},"date":{"wt":"1971"},"origyear":{"wt":"Reprinted from 1929"},"publisher":{"wt":"[[Oxford University Press]]"},"location":{"wt":"London"},"isbn":{"wt":""},"page":{"wt":""},"url":{"wt":""},"accessdate":{"wt":""}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA-U"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Arthur_Anthony_Macdonell" title="Arthur Anthony Macdonell" id="mwA-Y">Macdonell, Arthur Anthony</a> (1971) [Reprinted from 1929]. <i id="mwA-c">A practical Sanskrit dictionary with transliteration, accentuation and etymological analysis throughout</i>. London: <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press" id="mwA-g">Oxford University Press</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+practical+Sanskrit+dictionary+with+transliteration%2C+accentuation+and+etymological+analysis+throughout&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.aulast=Macdonell&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur+Anthony&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMeditation" class="Z3988" about="#mwt51" id="mwA-k"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt51" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwA-o"/></span></l